# Cursor Rules — Agent Bootstrap Hub
#
# Legacy format (.cursorrules). Also see .cursor/rules/agent-bootstrap.mdc for the
# Project Rules format supported by Cursor ≥ 0.43.
#
# Ensure this repo is open as a project/folder in Cursor for these rules to apply.

## Required: Load at Session Start

At the start of every session, you MUST:
1. Read `AGENTS.md` — single source of truth for all rules, roles, and workflows.
2. Read all 6 files in `memory-bank/` in order:
   projectbrief.md → productContext.md → systemPatterns.md → techContext.md → activeContext.md → progress.md
3. Read `manifest.yaml` — project registry; clone any missing repos listed there.
4. Read `skills/INDEX.md` — full skill catalog with trigger conditions.

These reads are non-optional. Do not skip them.

## Skill Invocation Rule

When any skill is triggered (see trigger conditions in skills/INDEX.md), read the full skill file before executing any steps. Do not rely on session memory of its contents.

## Skill Triggers (Quick Reference)

- `write-tests.md`              → any new feature, bug fix, or refactor — before writing code
- `debug-investigation.md`      → bug report, unexpected behavior, "fix this" without clear diagnosis
- `performance-profiling.md`    → "slow", "latency", "timeout", "optimize"
- `feature-flag-lifecycle.md`   → creating, rolling out, or graduating a feature flag
- `plan-code-review-workflow.md`→ any non-trivial task (>1 file, user-facing impact)
- `expert-pr-review.md`         → any PR review request
- `cherry-pick-to-release-branch.md` → hotfix or backport to a release branch
- `memory-bank-protocol.md`     → session start, project switch, new project setup
- `docs-protocol.md`            → creating or updating technical docs or ADRs

## Key Principles

- Always use absolute paths for file operations.
- Never commit or push unless explicitly instructed by the user.
- Request confirmation before deletions or destructive changes.
- Run all terminal commands non-interactively.
- TDD is mandatory: write a failing test before production code (docs/shared/tdd-standard.md).
- Update memory-bank/activeContext.md and progress.md at the end of every task.

## Supported Workflows

- "Follow the plan-code-review workflow to [task]"
- "Use the expert-pr-review skill on PR #N in repo X"
- "Switch to project 'eg' per manifest.yaml"
- "Debug [issue] using the debug-investigation skill"
- "Profile [operation] using the performance-profiling skill"
- "Follow the write-tests skill for [feature]"

See `AGENTS.md` for the complete ruleset, role definitions, and full skill catalog.
